We had a meeting where, you know, we didn't have a rule in place, now we want to change it right away on something.

567
00:57:42,866 --> 00:57:47,770
I think it's better to think about it and deal with it now as opposed to sometime in the future.

568
00:57:48,130 --> 00:57:57,977
And I don't have a thought in mind and say that we try to push in the traffic commission, say three minutes, but we often go beyond that because there's some valuable discussion, so.

569
00:57:59,178 --> 00:58:11,787
So I was just curious for clarification, Chief, you mean that you're limiting the amount of time a particular individual, not the entire section of comments from the general public?

570
00:58:12,856 --> 00:58:17,197
Uh, I, my, my intent was individuals because I don't know how much time we'll ever have.

571
00:58:17,357 --> 00:58:22,658
I mean, we may have a number of items on an agenda and only have a small, we often have only a small window for public comment.

572
00:58:23,298 --> 00:58:30,100
Um, if we, if we say, Hey, listen, the last half hours for public comment, we're limited in our HSE to only an hour meeting.

573
00:58:30,140 --> 00:58:37,641
So, I mean, I guess it can be thought of in both terms, but it's sort of the individual is what other commissions and committees.

574
00:58:38,381 --> 00:58:41,022
And that certainly makes sense because then it just.

575
00:58:41,893 --> 00:58:44,794
allows people to just be concise with their comments.

576
00:58:44,854 --> 00:58:48,735
And there can be some back and forth then, but not to go on.

577
00:58:48,755 --> 00:58:51,636
I mean, I don't think that's a bad rule.

578
00:58:52,097 --> 00:58:52,277
Yeah.

579
00:58:52,457 --> 00:58:58,239
And we can certainly look at if the comments provoke questions from the commissioners, then they're allowed to speak for it.

580
00:58:58,359 --> 00:59:07,002
I mean, it's, I think it depends on the conversation typewise, but it has come in handy and other commissions and committees and just a platform.

581
00:59:09,666 --> 00:59:14,310
Yeah, I think it's important because it also helps set expectations.

582
00:59:14,570 --> 00:59:20,935
And so, you know, there's, there's the commissioner's agenda that we must get through for our meeting.

583
00:59:21,556 --> 00:59:27,040
And then X amount of time is allocated for public comments.

584
00:59:30,263 --> 00:59:30,844
I know that.

585
00:59:31,964 --> 00:59:32,405
Sorry.

586
00:59:32,865 --> 00:59:33,326
I know that.

587
00:59:37,118 --> 00:59:38,639
What, are we going to box now?

588
00:59:39,899 --> 00:59:51,683
I know that in the meeting that I'm the liaison for, when it's open up for public participation, I believe the language is, we will now open up for public participation.

589
00:59:51,763 --> 00:59:58,545
Please note that each member of the public is, you know, is allowed to speak for two minutes on

590
00:59:59,713 --> 01:00:05,719
specific area of topic or whatever.

591
01:00:06,119 --> 01:00:14,908
Should there be time, then you may return to speak on other areas, but you can't stay like 10 minutes on something.

592
01:00:14,968 --> 01:00:17,871
So I could ask if it's written somewhere.

593
01:00:17,891 --> 01:00:19,232
I think it's written somewhere.

594
01:00:20,667 --> 01:00:24,849
Go ahead, Chief, we know you read the notes and everything.

595
01:00:26,310 --> 01:00:38,195
So Steve just put a great question in the chat and it's, you know, do we do our business at the end of our meeting, open it up to public participation?

596
01:00:38,235 --> 01:00:39,716
And I do think that should be part of it.

597
01:00:39,916 --> 01:00:48,360
But my thought process is when we do, if we get to a vote, right, where the Human Rights Commission has a motion

598
01:00:49,978 --> 01:00:57,044
perhaps we should entertain some public comment prior to the commission taking a vote, a public comment.

599
01:00:57,104 --> 01:01:10,756
I mean, it does make for longer meetings, et cetera, but I think, you know, you wouldn't want to, you know, everyone votes positive and at the end of the meeting say, hey, listen, I wish you hadn't voted on this because of this, this, and this.

600
01:01:10,776 --> 01:01:15,420
So you can allow for public comment on just the motion,

601
01:01:16,241 --> 01:01:21,903
and then still have a public comment at the end of the meeting that could be anything.

602
01:01:22,023 --> 01:01:23,663
I have a question of the Human Rights Commission.

603
01:01:23,943 --> 01:01:25,383
How do I join the Human Rights Commission?

604
01:01:25,423 --> 01:01:26,004
That sort of thing.

605
01:01:26,284 --> 01:01:30,985
So it's actually a pretty valid question to put in the chat.

606
01:01:31,805 --> 01:01:41,808
Yeah, it does seem as though people might have important information that would be really valuable to hear at the time of deliberation as opposed to the end.

607
01:01:42,931 --> 01:01:51,283
Again, if it was limited and pertinent to the particular thing we're voting on, that seems reasonable to me.

608
01:01:51,704 --> 01:01:57,673
And if in fact we have to take a little more time to do it, it seems like the right thing to do.

609
01:01:57,693 --> 01:01:59,035
Agreed.

610
01:02:00,142 --> 01:02:12,405
As a matter of fact, I just, I think, Chief, what you said is the way it works on the floor, which is emotion is, you know, emotion is brought forward.

611
01:02:12,425 --> 01:02:15,766
You know, people discuss blah, blah, blah, blah, blah.

612
01:02:16,406 --> 01:02:28,870
And then, you know, any members of the public should be able to speak on that motion because I might want to say no, but a member of the public could end up saying something and then it's, you know,

613
01:02:30,190 --> 01:02:44,897
It could change the way I choose to vote, and then the commissioners should vote but I just I want to make sure that folks understand that it's for the motion, it's not to direct the work of the commissioners it's not the public meeting.

614
01:02:45,897 --> 01:02:48,979
space to say other things.

615
01:02:49,139 --> 01:02:54,482
It's specifically pertains to the motion that is on the floor.

616
01:02:55,203 --> 01:03:09,351
And I think if the chair recognizes and says, we'll open it up to public comment on this motion, the chair will, we have two minutes, three minutes, whatever we say, and then we move forward because I think that can be valuable information gained prior to a vote from people outside of us.

617
01:03:10,051 --> 01:03:13,233
And then at the end, you could still say,

618
01:03:14,097 --> 01:03:23,022
Now general questions about procedure or whatever, as you're saying, you know, how do I join or whatever would be very appropriate at the end.

619
01:03:23,522 --> 01:03:25,022
Definitely, definitely.

620
01:03:25,603 --> 01:03:26,163
I like that.

621
01:03:26,863 --> 01:03:27,624
Good work, Steve.

622
01:03:30,225 --> 01:03:31,506
You've seen a few meetings.

623
01:03:36,908 --> 01:03:43,512
